Long story short--way too much destruction that was often difficult to follow at times. And who ends up paying for all that destruction? Stark? The government? Or both? Without question, the cast was awesome as usual, including the voice of Ultron, James Spader. The slow-mo scenes of everyone fighting was very cool for sure. But the scene where the Hulk goes berserk was way too long. I would have cut the time in half on that part. I was getting somewhat bored after a while.

